{
  "stem": "25423.5",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's sort of a black cassock with a leather belt, which a novice wears.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had normal clothing because this was used only during services in church, but not in work.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Normal clothes, pants, shirt.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had a little lambswool sort of a-- I looked like dressed like a peasant.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I assume that it must have been September 1900-- first week of September 1944.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Soviets liberated the city in June 1944.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I stayed through July and most of August in the city, in the monastery.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The decision for me to leave was made by Klyment, the brother of the metropolitan.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Metropolitan was very ill.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He died three months later.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Secondly, Klyment told me, before you leave Poland, finish your education because, otherwise, you're can not to go to a university.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Remember, that you have to finish your university studies.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And if you get out after the war, go to Rome and report what you have seen.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "When I have provided him with the decision that I intend to go-- so in the monastery, it was arranged, first of all, to provide me with shirts.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In those days, it was a major effort to make sure that I have a decent pair of shoes, socks, clothing.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They looked into their chest to find some money and gave me what they had.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Gave me a bottle of wine, some bread.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the night before I left, the monks, after services, came to my cell one by one, saying goodbye.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And everybody brought a little gift.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Whatever they had, which means a picture-- the holy pictures, which they have-- a prayer book, a pair of socks, a handkerchief.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was like a family sending a member of the family away.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Then I was asked to come to the residence of the metropolitan.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
